data.text:
Shawn Marion - Points

Shawn Marion scores a career high 44 points (2006)

On February 22, 2006, Shawn Marion set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 44 points in Phoenix's home win against Boston, 103-94. He also had 15 rebounds, 4 steals and 3 blocks. He shot 11/15 from two, 4/7 from three, shooting at 68.2% from the field. He also shot 10/10 from the free-throw line.

Shawn Marion - Rebounds

Shawn Marion grabs a career high 24 rebounds (2006)

On February 25, 2006, Shawn Marion tied his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 24 rebounds in Phoenix's home win against Charlotte, 136-121. He also had 31 points, 3 assists, 1 steal and 2 blocks.

Shawn Marion - Assists

Shawn Marion gives a career high 8 assists (2000)

On November 29, 2000, Shawn Marion tied his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 8 assists in Phoenix's road loss against Vancouver, 109-106. He also had 14 points, 19 rebounds, 1 steal and 3 blocks.

Shawn Marion - Steals

Shawn Marion has a career high 8 steals (2006)

On February 06, 2006, Shawn Marion set his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 8 steals in Phoenix's home loss against Minnesota, 101-103. He also had 14 points, 12 rebounds and 3 assists.

Shawn Marion - Blocks

Shawn Marion blocks a career high 6 shots (2004)

On December 13, 2004, Shawn Marion tied his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 6 blocks in Phoenix's home win against Orlando, 121-100. He also had 19 points, 10 rebounds and 3 assists.
